  "prompt": "Can I write C# on a Mac?",
  "response": "Yes, you can write C# on a Mac using several methods:\n\n1. Visual Studio for Mac\n- Official IDE from Microsoft\n- Free with Community Edition\n- Full-featured C# development environment\n- Supports .NET Core and Xamarin development\n\n2. Visual Studio Code\n- Free, lightweight code editor\n- Cross-platform\n- Requires installing .NET SDK\n- Has excellent C# extensions\n\n3. JetBrains Rider\n- Professional IDE for .NET development\n- Paid software\n- Supports cross-platform .NET development\n- Very powerful and feature-rich\n\n4. Mono Framework\n- Open-source .NET implementation\n- Allows running .NET applications on Mac\n- Can be used with various text editors\n\n5. .NET Core SDK\n- Microsoft's cross-platform .NET framework\n- Can be installed directly on macOS\n- Allows command-line and IDE development\n\nRecommended steps:\n1. Install .NET SDK\n2. Choose an IDE or code editor\n3. Install C# extensions if using VS Code\n4. Start developing!\n\nEach method has pros and cons, so choose based on your specific needs and preferences.",
